Description:
**SOLD BY PAUL RINGERI**
ACACIA ESTATE, BOTANIC RIDGE: **WIDE 24 METRE FRONTAGE** Searching for a tranquil location? Requiring an estate offering family friendly living? This is a sensational opportunity for those looking to upsize or downsize in a secluded pocket surrounded by quality housing!
Titled and ready to go 3 Gumflats Way is ideal for those looking to reside within a thriving development with a million dollar outlook. You will be, literally, within paces of spacious parkland and maturing waterways.
The generously sized surrounding lots cater precisely for expansive homes and provide the sense of space that local residents are seeking to enjoy. The scene is set for a lifestyle full of peace and privacy.
The land itself is truly a prime piece of real estate and provides the perfect foundation to create your dream home. Regular in shape the land measures a healthy 1,080m2 with a wide frontage of 24m and a depth of 45m. There is ample room for an array of different styles and designs so what are you waiting for? Head down to the local display village or start designing a suitable custom concept that caters for bonus side access plus room for a pool or rear shedding (S.T.C.A.)!
Named after the Australian wattle, Acacia is designed to blend perfectly with the natural environment, including the Royal Botanic Gardens positioned directly next door. Acacia includes beautifully landscaped parks, designed wetlands and wide tree lined streets. Other features include the proposed Botanic Village, a local shopping hub with its own supermarket, cafe and speciality stores, Botanic Ridge primary school and even a community centre. Sports and recreational fields are also planned!
Sensational location within close proximity to all of the amenities on offer in the established townships of Cranbourne and Pearcedale. If you are a golf enthusiast chuck the clubs in the boot as the well known 18 hole Greg Norman designed course is only a brisk drive away!
Call today before it's GOING, GOING ..... GONE!
CONTACT US TO ARRANGE FOR A TIME TO VIEW THE SECTION 32 VENDOR STATEMENT!

Description:
Feel right at home
Located in the Settlers Run estate surrounding by one of the top golf courses designed by legendary golfer Greg Norman is this stunning, family home boasting so much more than just its location. House features include;
- Four spacious bedrooms, master located downstairs with a WIR and full ensuite.
- Three separate spacious living areas allows you to entertain family and friends with an open plan kitchen overlooking the family meals area as well as the living room upstairs with your own hide away wet bar overlooking your stunning city views.
- The kitchen is an entertainers' dream with stone benchtops throughout, hard timber flooring and a 900mm Smeg oven.
The property also offers you refrigerated cooling and heating for all year-round comfort, as well as a double car lock up garage with internal and drive through access to the backyard. Located within walking distance to the Settlers Run Club house, relax while overlooking the 18th green at the clubhouse restaurant/ bar or perhaps go for a swim or spa after a workout at the clubhouse gym. Botanic Ridge truly does offer a desirable lifestyle with everything you need at your front door. So, don't wait call us today to inspect.

Description:
FAMILY FRIENDLY - CASCADES ON CLYDE
CRANBOURNE EAST - CASCADES ON CLYDE - Set in the family-friendly estate of Cascades on Clyde this home would suit a young family or first home buyer. Within walking distance to parklands, 2 shopping precincts, medical facilities, sporting facilities and Wilandra Rise Primary School.
Offering 4 bedrooms, master with full ensuite and walk-in robe. Light and bright living areas and functional floor plan for day to day living.
Central kitchen with island benchtop and modern appliances will be the hub of this home, cooking for the family will be a delight and convenient.
Features include:
-Ducted heating
-Split system
-Play equipment and cubby house for the kids to enjoy
-Garden shed
-Double remote garage with internal access
-Dishwasher and stainless steel appliances
Surrounded by top-end properties and is within walking distance to picturesque wetlands, this home boasts convenience. Other estate features include Class-A recycled water ensuring lush gardens year-round, over 14 hectares of parkland and public open space, public BBQ facilities, playgrounds and walking tracks.
Those who are business savvy will appreciate this Telstra smart community positioned within a short drive to all amenities located in the townships of Berwick, Clyde and Cranbourne. Minutes away from freeway access en route to the Melbourne CBD, the popular Clyde Primary School, Casey Fields football ground/Casey Race aquatic centre and the Town Centre. Not to mention just minutes away from the Selandra Rise and Hunt Club village shopping centres.

Description:
Glamourous Style in Cascades on Clyde
Brilliantly designed four bedroom home on 622m2 is minutes to Cascades on Clyde wetlands, parklands and Selandra Rise shopping precinct. Offering enduring appeal through its subtle flair, numerous features and zoned layout. Combined with three living spaces, outdoor entertaining and a spacious sunlit backyard, the home caters marvellously for every family, every lifestyle.
Boasting a light and bright neutral interior, the tiled entrance hall opens upon the formal lounge seamlessly flowing through to the entertainer's kitchen. Here the hub of the home with S/S appliances and breakfast bench overlooks the meals, living room and alfresco - creating superb indoor / outdoor amenities for relaxing with family and friends. Additionally, the separate rumpus lends itself to a fun filled kid's zone.
Complemented by a further three sizeable bedrooms with BIRs, the master at the front of the home boasts dual sink ensuite and fitted WIR. Stylish family bathroom with bath, shower and separate powder room, good sized laundry and DLUG with internal access. Other notable features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, ample storage and low maintenance garden.
Enjoying a most family friendly location being close to Cranbourne East PS, Secondary College, and an easy stroll only minutes to public transport.
*Contact agent to arrange a private inspection

Description:
**SOLD BY PAUL RINGERI**
CRANBOURNE WEST: **FLEXIBLE FLOORPLAN OFFERING THE OPTION FOR A 4TH BEDROOM, 2ND LIVING ZONE, CHILDREN'S RETREAT OR A HOME OFFICE**
Presented in stunning near new condition, 43 Middleham Close, is proudly offered to the market for the first time. With many happy memories created over the past 17 years, the current owners are eager to find a new family who can enjoy living in this established neighbourhood as much as they have!
Nestled in the quietest of court-style locations, in close proximity to walking tracks and bus stops, you will have easy access to all required local amenities and major arterials.
With its timeless facade and pristine garden setting combining to provide a sensational first impression, the home itself features a generous lounge with adjoining dining room complete with timber look flooring. A modernised hostess kitchen is complete with a breakfast bar and provides convenient external sliding door access.
There are 3 generous robed bedrooms, including the master with walk in wardrobe and a perfectly maintained ensuite that compliments the family bathroom and separate second toilet. Not to mention the additional multi-purpose zone that can act as the perfect 4th bedroom, 2nd living area, children's retreat or home office!
Ducted heating, evaporative cooling and a split system air conditioner provide seasonal respite, whilst outside you will be greeted by a single garage with gated side access and a lengthy driveway allowing provisions for additional parking facilities.
With an overall land size of app. 572m2, the generous rear yard offers an abundance of space for those with kids and pets, and features the perfect entertainer's pergola - you are sure to be the toast of the town come Bathurst and Grand Final day!
The location is second to none within moments of multiple train stations, public/private schooling, child care facilities and the Camms Road, Sandhurst and Marriot Waters shopping centres. Literally minutes to the Cranbourne town centre and major roads leading to the beach, mountain ranges and the CBD!
Offering fantastic value for money this gem is bound to be snapped up quickly so call before it's SELLING, SELLING, SOLD!

Modern Classic In Campaspe
Located only minutes drive from local schools, shops, and public transport, this immaculate home provides a fantastic opportunity for those looking for a property with nothing to be desired. Presented as close to brand new and beautifully established, it will leave a lasting impression.
The property has been adorned with all the latest colours and decor, giving it a fresh modern feel throughout. Large accommodation includes master bedroom with a stunning full ensuite and walk in robe, whilst a further two bedrooms are located at the rear of the home and serviced by the main bathroom and laundry. Indoor/outdoor living & entertaining has never been easier, with a fully appointed modern styled kitchen including 900m stove, stone benches and the adjoining open plan living room which flows out to a decked alfresco and landscaped rear yard. Description:
Eve Estate - 24sqs of luxury on 572sqm block
Secure yourself a fantastic property located in Eve Estate and situated on a generous size block of 572sqm.
This well presented home showcases three bedrooms, two bathrooms & a study. The master bedroom features an ensuite and walk-in robe, whilst the additional bedrooms have double built in wardrobes.
There is no shortage of space, with a large open plan living and meals area which sits adjacent to a spacious formal lounge that also has the ability to be closed off for privacy with double door entry.
If you love to entertain, this home also features access from the kitchen/living area to your very own decked alfresco via double glass sliding doors.
With only minutes away from the Estate's shopping precinct, local schools, cafes, public transport and easy access to the M1, this is an ideal location perfect for any family.
Key features:
• 3 bedroom and study (possible 4th bedroom)
• 2 bathroom
• Master bedroom with ensuite and WIR
• Spacious living areas
• Decked alfresco area
• Stainless steel appliances in kitchen
• Ducted heating & evaporative cooling
• Low maintenance yard
• Double garage with internal access
• Close proximity to shops, transport & schools

31 NAGLE CRESCENT, CRANBOURNE WEST
Goldbank Real Estate presents this opportunity to own the home of your dreams. Proudly positioned in the premier Clarinda Park Estate is this perfect sized family home boasting with an abundance of style, space and offering an outstanding lifestyle.
If you are looking for a property that offers outstanding value for money with nothing to do but move in, you have come to the right address. This perfectly presented home is appealing for first home buyers, downsizers or investors.

This property needs to be on your "must see" list this weekend!

Description:
Gardenia - Please call for inspection arrangements
Nestled in a quiet, cul-de-sac court, is this family residence built in the 1980's on a 614sqm (approx.) allotment. The three-bedroom, two-bathroom home has plenty of character and charm including cathedral ceilings, exposed brick walls, colonial windows, new floating wooden floors and a stained-glass entrance. The comfortable lounge area filled with natural light outlooks onto the tropical front garden while the light-filled kitchen has views of the alfresco and showcases a gas stove-top, updated range hood, oven and an osmosis filtered water system. The master suite has a walk-thru-robe and sizeable en suite with spa bath, while the two bedrooms have built in robes and share a separate bathroom. An entertainer's delight there is a significant covered alfresco deck area with built in BBQ and private yard featuring ample space for children to play. Other additions include a laundry, Ultimate fireplace, gas ducted heating, split system air conditioners, a remote double garage, a single carport and side access to the property. Close to transport, shops, cafes and restaurants.
- Quiet, private property in cul-de-sac court
- Family residence, built in 1980's
- Cathedral ceilings & colonial windows
- Wooden timber floors & stained-glass entrance
- Living area filled with natural light
- Master suite with walk-thru-robe & ensuite
- Significant alfresco deck area with built in BBQ
- Private yard with ample space
- Ultimate fireplace & gas ducted heating
- Split system air conditioners
- Remote double garage & single carport
- Close to transport, shops & cafes
Photo I.D. required at all Inspections.

Description:
A HIDDEN GEM
Set amidst a native garden and quality housing, is this unique opportunity to add your finishing touch. Offering warmth and convenience the property comprises of three bedrooms, master with full ensuite. Each of the remaining bedrooms is a generous size and feature built in robes.
A hostess kitchen is family friendly with an array of cupboard and bench space that adjoins an open plan living and meals room, complete with extended ceilings and ducted heating. A second separate living room is more formal and offers a quiet retreat.
While a sun drenched paved outdoor area offers plenty of room to entertain. All set upon a spacious allotment of 702sqm (app). A stroll from schools and parkland.

Description:
INSPECT BY APPOINTMENT ONLY 5 Bedroom Family favourite in the Heart of Clyde North!
IMPORTANT INFORMATION - *** COVID-19 Response Strategy ***
We are no longer able to conduct open for inspections, however we welcome private viewings to qualified buyers. Please contact the listing agent to arrange a private viewing
This beautifully presented home comes with room for a growing family, consisting of 5 double sized bedrooms, master with ceiling fan, ensuite and walk in robe and secondary bedrooms with mirrored built in robes.
Open planned kitchen featuring 900mm freestanding stainless steel oven/cook top, 2 sets of double built in pantry & dishwasher overlooking the huge dining and lounge area. There is also the potential to open up one of the bedrooms and convert it into a second living area should you require 2 living zones, this home is one that comes with endless potential to call home!
Situated on a generously sized block of approx.. 438m2 this home comes with pristine low maintenance gardens and Colourbond fencing, gas ducted heating, cooling, high ceilings, security camera system, alarm system, double remote garage with rear and internal access and much much more!
Located in the Heart of Clyde Norths Selandra Rise Estate youre within proximity to Wilandra Rise primary school, St. Peters secondary collage & Selandra Rise shopping centre, and only a few minutes drive to freeway access, Clyde Primary School, Casey RACE Recreation & Aquatic Centre and Casey Indoor Sports Centre.
Call today to find out more about this beauty before its too late!
*** PLEASE NOTE ***
We have obtained all information in this listing from sources that we believe to be highly reliable; however, we cannot guarantee its accuracy. Prospective purchasers are advised to carry out their own investigations.

Description:
DREAMS DO COME TRUE
CLYDE NORTH: In search of a place to call "Home Sweet Home"? Your search ends here. Welcome to No 10 Buckskin Drive, Clyde North, located in one of the most sought after estate in the area, the prestigious Selandra Rise Estate.
This impressive family home is the perfect opportunity for anyone who is thinking of building, but wants to avoid the pain of waiting for years. Neatly positioned on a low maintenance block, this is bound to impress first home buyers, investors and people who are looking to upsize.
Added internal and external features;
* Approximately 540 sqm land
* Built in 2013
* Two separate living zones
* Plenty of natural light through to the house
* Alfresco & extended outdoor under cover area
* Potential side access for a boat or caravan
* En suite with two vanities
* 900 mm five burner cook top & 600 mm oven
* Dishwasher
* Double door pantry
* Glass splash back
* Ducted heating
* Split system air conditioner
* Walk in linen
* High ceilings
- Selandra Rise Shopping Centre is approx. 6 minutes' walk away from the house
- Access to public transport is approx. 2 minutes' drive away from the house
- Wilandra Rise Primary is approx. 2 minutes' drive away from the house
- St.Thomas the Apostle Primary School is approx. 4 minutes' drive away from the house
- St.Peters Secondary College is approximately about 2 minutes' drive away from the house
- Casey Fields is approx. 6 minutes' drive away from the house
- Casey Race, YMCA Gym/Pool & Library are located approx. 6 minutes' drive away from house
- Within walking distance to bike paths, playgrounds, parks, sports facilities & community vegetable garden
**PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT ALL INSPECTIONS**
